Whereas many older people in the United States lack the reading, math, or English skills to read a
			 prescription and follow medical instructions, endangering their lives and
			 the lives of their loved ones;

Whereas many individuals who are unemployed, underemployed, or receive public assistance lack the
			 literacy skills to obtain and keep a job with a family-sustaining income,
			 continue their education, or participate in job training programs;

Whereas many high school dropouts do not have the literacy skills to complete their education,
			 transition to postsecondary education or vocational training, or become
			 employed;

